humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: According to the report, all assessed lymph nodes are negative for metastatic carcinoma (rules 8, 11). Specifically, sentinel lymph nodes 1 to 6 in the left axilla are negative for carcinoma (diagnosis sections D, I, J, and K). Therefore, the N stage is N0.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report states 'Lymph nodes: Sentinel lymph node only. Lymph node status: Negative 0/8.' This indicates that there is no evidence of cancer in the sentinel lymph nodes, which would correspond to an N0 stage. The number of lymph nodes examined and the absence of cancer in those nodes supports this classification. The N stage is a classification of the spread of cancer to the lymph nodes and an N0 stage indicates that the cancer has not spread to the lymph nodes.
